HB 876 Original 2026 Regular Session Robby Carter
Abstract: Provides relative to litigation costs associated with medical liens.
Present law (R.S. 9:4752) provides that a healthcare provider, hospital, or ambulance service
that furnishes services or supplies to any injured person shall have a privilege for the
reasonable charges or fees.
Proposed law retains present law and provides that a healthcare provider, hospital, or
ambulance service shall be responsible for up to 20% of litigation costs, as ordered by the
court.
(Amends R.S. 9:4752)
